<br>
If the guy asking 2k can't sell it quickly, he'll give up/log off/etc and come back to try again some other time.  In the end everyone benefits.  Since you, the buyer, can't watch the bazaar 24/7 to catch the seller online, the retail guy holds the spell for you and charges a fee for the service.  Yeah, sometimes it's a rather large fee, but you don't have to pay it.  If you really don't think an item or spell is worth the cost then don't buy it, it's as simple as that.<br>
<br>
imo so long as someone doesn't spend their whole time stockpiling spells and doesn't succeed in bottlenecking the whole spell economy for personal benefit then nothing's wrong.<br>
